underlying_goal: To fix URL formatting in a LaTeX paper and commit the changes.
friction_detail: Claude was initially confused about whether the compiled PDF was gitignored, as the CLAUDE.md documentation contradicted the actual .gitignore file. It correctly resolved this by checking recent commit history.
primary_success: Claude correctly diagnosed the URL formatting issue, added the `xurl` package, configured `hyperref`, and then correctly handled a discrepancy between documentation and git state to commit all necessary files.
brief_summary: The user wanted to fix URL line breaking in a LaTeX document. Claude added the `xurl` package to fix it. While committing, it noticed a discrepancy between documentation (saying the PDF was ignored) and reality (it was tracked), correctly deduced it should commit the PDF based on history, and pushed the changes.
